ican_english/the-federal-bureau-of-investigation\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">the Federal Bureau of Investigation</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-federal-bureau-of-investigation\">the Federal Bureau of Investigation</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["federal adjective","the Federal Aviation Administration","the Federal Bureau of Investigation noun","the Federal Communications Commission","the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation"]},{"name":"CID","pos":"abbreviation","content":"<div class=\"entry\" htag=\"section\" hlength=\"3\" id=\"cid\" sk=\"cid: :10\" sum=\"281\" hclass=\"entry\" idm_id=\"000010522\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"cid_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" id=\"cid_h_1\" htag=\"h1\" hclass=\"headword\">CID</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">abbreviation</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\" wd=\"cid\" hclass=\"phons_br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/c/cid/cid__/cid__gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/c/cid/cid__/cid__gb_1.ogg\" title=\"cid pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌsiː aɪ ˈdiː/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"cid\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"n_am\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/c/cid/cid__/cid__us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/c/cid/cid__/cid__us_1.ogg\" title=\"cid pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌsiː aɪ ˈdiː/</span></div></span> </div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"cid_sng_1\" hclass=\"sense\" fkcefr=\"c2\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\"><div class=\"variants\" hclass=\"variants\" type=\"ff\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"v-g\"><span class=\"v\">Criminal Investigation Department</span></span></div> (the department of the British police force that is responsible for solving crimes)</span></span><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"cid_unbox_1\" unbox=\"cult\"><span class=\"box_title\">Culture <span class=\"closed\">law enforcement</span></span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">law enforcement</span><span class=\"p\">Britain has regional <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/police-force\" title=\"police forces definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">police forces</span></a></span>, which are responsible for maintaining <span class=\"eb\">law and order</span> in their own area. London has two police forces, the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-metropolitan-police#the_metropolitan_police_topg_1\" title=\"Metropolitan Police definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Metropolitan Police</span></a>, often referred to as the <span class=\"eb\">Met</span>, which covers <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/greater-london\" title=\"Greater London definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Greater London</span></a> and has its <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/headquarters\" title=\"headquarters definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">headquarters</span></a> at <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/new-scotland-yard\" title=\"New Scotland Yard definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">New Scotland Yard</span></a>, and the smaller <span class=\"eb\">City of London Police</span>.</span><span class=\"p\">Each regional police force is led by a <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/chief-constable\" title=\"chief constable definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">chief constable</span></a></span>. In England and Wales since 2012 there have been directly elected <span class=\"eb\">Police and Crime Commissioners</span> who direct the work of the chief constable and his or her force. Police officers wear dark blue uniforms, and <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/constable\" title=\"constables definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">constables</span></a> and <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sergeant\" title=\"sergeants definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">sergeants</span></a> in some forces sometimes wear tall hard <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/helmet\" title=\"helmets definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">helmets</span></a> <span class=\"gloss\" hclass=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\">(= hard hats that protect the head)</span>. Some members of the public are trained as <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/special-constable\" title=\"special constables definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">special constables</span></a></span> and are available to help the police in an emergency.</span><span class=\"p\">Each police force has a <span class=\"eb\">Criminal Investigation Department</span> (<span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/cid\" title=\"CID definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">CID</span></a></span>) of detectives. CID officers are chosen from the uniformed police. They do not wear uniforms and have the title Detective before their rank, for example Detective Sergeant Jones. Individual police forces have other special units for areas such as traffic, child protection, etc. The Metropolitan Police has <span class=\"eb\">Counter Terrorism Command</span> which works to prevent <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/terrorism\" title=\"terrorism definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">terrorism</span></a> and some other police forces have a <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/special-branch\" title=\"Special Branch definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Special Branch</span></a></span> to do the same job. The <span class=\"eb\">National Crime Agency</span> was set up to fight organised crime at a national and international level.</span><span class=\"p\">Police officers in Britain generally carry only <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/baton\" title=\"batons definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">batons</span></a> <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= long clubs)</span> as weapons, although they may also have a <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/tasertm\" title=\"Taser definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Taser</span></a> or a special kind of <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/spray_1\" title=\"spray definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">spray</span></a> to defend themselves with. Only certain officers, who have had special training, carry a gun. Police forces are trying to build better relationships with local communities, a practice called <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/community-policing\" title=\"community policing definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">community policing</span></a></span>. More police now <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/patrol_1\" title=\"patrol definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">patrol</span></a> on foot, instead of in police cars, so that they have more contact with people.</span><span class=\"p\">In the US, <span class=\"eb\">law <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/enforcement\" title=\"enforcement definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">enforcement</span></a></span> is carried out by different organizations at the various levels of government. There are many thousands of <span class=\"eb\">law enforcement agencies</span>. At national level, the <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/fbi\" title=\"FBI definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">FBI</span></a></span> (<span class=\"eb\">Federal Bureau of Investigation</span>) employs <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/special-agent\" title=\"special agents definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">special agents</span></a></span>, who investigate crimes across the US. At state level, <span class=\"eb\">state police departments</span> are responsible for <span class=\"eb\">highway patrols</span> and their officers are called <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/state-trooper#state_trooper_topg_1\" title=\"state troopers definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">state troopers</span></a></span>. Each county within a state has an elected <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sheriff\" title=\"sheriff definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">sheriff</span></a></span> and the people who work in the sheriff's office, <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/deputy\" title=\"deputies definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">deputies</span></a></span>, are responsible for investigating crimes. Cities have their own police departments. They may be very large in cities like New York, but those in small towns have only a few officers. Most colleges and universities have their own small police forces.</span><span class=\"p\">The members of the US police force who have most contact with the public are uniformed officers, who patrol usually in cars or sometimes on foot and are the first to arrive when a crime is reported. More serious crimes are investigated by detectives, who usually wear <span class=\"eb\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/plain-clothes_1\" title=\"plain clothes definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">plain clothes</span></a></span> <span class=\"gloss\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"gloss\">(= normal clothes)</span> instead of a uniform. Police officers in the US usually carry a gun.</span></span></span></div><span class=\"topic-g\"><span class=\"prefix\">Topics </span><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/law-and-justice?level=c2\" title=\"Topic law-and-justice\"><span class=\"topic\" href=\"l2:politics_and_society:law_and_justice?cefr=c2\"><span class=\"topic_name\">Law and justice</span><span class=\"topic_cefr\">c2</span></span></a></span>    \n</li></ol><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/cid\">CID</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["Ciaran","cicada noun","CID abbreviation","-cidal suffix","-cide combining form"]},{"name":"FBI","pos":"abbreviation","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sk=\"fbi: :10\" id=\"fbi\" hlength=\"3\" htag=\"section\" hclass=\"entry\" sum=\"409\" idm_id=\"000021437\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"fbi_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" htag=\"h1\" id=\"fbi_h_1\" hclass=\"headword\">FBI</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">abbreviation</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\" wd=\"fbi\" hclass=\"phons_br\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/f/fbi/fbi__/fbi__gb_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/f/fbi/fbi__/fbi__gb_1.ogg\" title=\"fbi pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌef biː ˈaɪ/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"fbi\" geo=\"n_am\" htag=\"div\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/f/fbi/fbi__/fbi__us_1.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/f/fbi/fbi__/fbi__us_1.ogg\" title=\"fbi pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˌef biː ˈaɪ/</span></div></span> </div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"fbi_sng_1\" hclass=\"sense\" fkcefr=\"c1\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" hclass=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\"><div class=\"variants\" htag=\"div\" type=\"ff\" hclass=\"variants\"><span class=\"v-g\"><span class=\"v\">Federal Bureau of Investigation</span></span></div> (the police department in the US that is controlled by the national government and that is responsible for dealing with crimes that affect more than one state)</span></span><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" source=\"ald9_guide\" unbox=\"cult\" id=\"fbi_unbox_1\"><span class=\"box_title\">Culture</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">The FBI is also responsible for the safety of the country from international enemies. It publishes a 'Ten Most Wanted List' of the most dangerous criminals. The FBI, which is part of the US Department of Justice, was created in 1908 as the Bureau of Investigation, and took its present name in 1935.<span class=\"xrefs\" xt=\"see\" hclass=\"xrefs\" htag=\"span\"><span class=\"prefix\">see also</span> <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/j-edgar-hoover\" title=\"J Edgar Hoover definition\"><span class=\"xr-g\" bord=\"n\" href=\"jedgarhoover_hm2_ge\"><span class=\"xh\">J Edgar Hoover</span></span></a></span></span></span></span></div><span class=\"topic-g\"><span class=\"prefix\">Topics </span><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/law-and-justice?level=c1\" title=\"Topic law-and-justice\"><span class=\"topic\" href=\"l2:politics_and_society:law_and_justice?cefr=c1\"><span class=\"topic_name\">Law and justice</span><span class=\"topic_cefr\">c1</span></span></a></span>    \n</li></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/fbi\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">FBI</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/fbi\">FBI</a></div></div>\n","matches":["FBI"],"relatives":["FBI"],"nearBys":["fayre noun","faze verb","FBI abbreviation","F-bomb noun","FC abbreviation"]}]]